Author: Nexus-Digital-Automations <founder1@nexusdigitalautomations.com>
Date:   Tue May 5 10:26:23 2026 -0500

    Auto-scale top_n ceiling so mass selector isn't silently capped on medium+ repos
    
    repo_index_top_n now defaults to 0 (auto), computing min(20 + n_tracked // 10, 100).
    A 300-file repo gets top_n=50, a 800-file repo gets 100 — the mass selector has room
    to reach its 80% coverage target instead of hitting a fixed-20 wall.
    
    Set repo_index_top_n explicitly to pin the ceiling.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>

